from tdaad.anomaly_detectors import TopologicalAnomalyDetector
detector = TopologicalAnomalyDetector(window_size=100, n_centers_by_dim=2, tda_max_dim=1).fit(X)
anomaly_score = detector.score_samples(X)

# Recuperation des intervalles de timestamps d'anomalies
index_anomaly=[]
file = open("machine-3-5.txt", "r")
while True:
    content=file.readline()
    if not content:
        break
    index_anomaly.append([int(content.split(":")[0].split("-")[0]),int(content.split(":")[0].split("-")[1])])
file.close()

print(index_anomaly)

# Analyse de la bonne detection par intervalle
nb_good=0
for i in range(0,len(index_anomaly)):
    res= np.sum( (index_pred >=index_anomaly[i][0]) & (index_pred <=index_anomaly[i][1]) )
    print("interval index", i, "  val", index_anomaly[i],"nb de point ok ", res, "sur une longueur de ",index_anomaly[i][1]- index_anomaly[i][0] )
    if res>0:
        nb_good+=1

print("nb interval anomalies identifiÃ©s", nb_good , "  sur"  , len(index_anomaly))
